Popular actress, Iyabo Ojo, has revealed her deep yearning to experience marriage yet again. Ojo via her Instagram page on Friday shared photos repping her maternal grandmother’s culture as she adorned an Edo bride attire for the first part of the reality TV show’s reunion expected to drop today. Feeling all nostalgic in her outfit, the mother of two confessed her look has ignited her desire to get married again.   Oxford University congratulates DJ Cuppy on thesis…     Estranged wife, Anita drags Paul Okoye to court over alleged…     Davido to feature on Chris Brown’s ‘Breezy’…   “Repping my grandmother’s culture (Edo State) from my Maternal side at the reunion #RHOLagos was indeed a thing of Joy for me…. “It’s Friday already & it’s all about the reunion, it’s all about the gbasgbos #RHOLagos showing only on Showmax.” “Carry me dey go, Jehovah carry me dey go my husband house. Now!!! with this Edo look I feel like getting married again #rholagos”, she wrote.